Alfred Hearn Healey (13 July 1875 – 9 September 1960) was a British athlete in the 1906 Intercalated Games and the 1908 Summer Olympics.He competed for Great Britain in the 1906 Intercalated Games held in Athens, Greece in the 110 metre hurdles where he won the silver medal. In the 100 metre event he was eliminated in the semi-finals.
Two years later he was also eliminated in the semi-finals of the 110 metre hurdles competition.
